WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:04.630 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:04.630 --> 00:00:05.600 align:middle line:90%


00:00:05.600 --> 00:00:09.360 align:middle line:84%
>> In many places on our
planet, men and women have left

00:00:09.360 --> 00:00:12.150 align:middle line:90%
mysterious traces behind them.

00:00:12.150 --> 00:00:14.820 align:middle line:84%
These are geoglyphs,
designs left

00:00:14.820 --> 00:00:19.920 align:middle line:84%
on hillsides or the ground
made by the hand of man.

00:00:19.920 --> 00:00:23.240 align:middle line:84%
Most of these designs have
been erased by passing time,

00:00:23.240 --> 00:00:26.100 align:middle line:84%
but some have passed
through history to reach us.

00:00:26.100 --> 00:00:28.650 align:middle line:84%
It's a miracle that we can
still admire some of them.

00:00:28.650 --> 00:00:35.770 align:middle line:90%


00:00:35.770 --> 00:00:38.530 align:middle line:84%
While no one knows the
name of their creators,

00:00:38.530 --> 00:00:42.900 align:middle line:84%
all the geoglyphs are shrouded
in mystery and legend.

00:00:42.900 --> 00:00:45.741 align:middle line:84%
What was it that led people to
conceive these enormous shapes

00:00:45.741 --> 00:00:47.740 align:middle line:84%
and to leave a message
in the ground which would

00:00:47.740 --> 00:00:49.630 align:middle line:90%
last throughout the millennia?

00:00:49.630 --> 00:00:53.320 align:middle line:84%
>> We know that gods and
goddesses were very important

00:00:53.320 --> 00:00:54.295 align:middle line:90%
way back in the past.

00:00:54.295 --> 00:00:55.910 align:middle line:90%


00:00:55.910 --> 00:00:58.790 align:middle line:84%
>> Really, making shapes,
carving them into the ground,

00:00:58.790 --> 00:01:01.300 align:middle line:84%
that's not too difficult.
On the other hand,

00:01:01.300 --> 00:01:03.800 align:middle line:84%
planning on such a big scale,
that's impressive work.

00:01:03.800 --> 00:01:06.420 align:middle line:90%


00:01:06.420 --> 00:01:10.060 align:middle line:84%
>> The Nazca civilization, which
is mainly known for its lines,

00:01:10.060 --> 00:01:11.520 align:middle line:90%
didn't just produce that.

00:01:11.520 --> 00:01:16.830 align:middle line:90%


00:01:16.830 --> 00:01:18.420 align:middle line:90%
>> He's iconic.

00:01:18.420 --> 00:01:20.290 align:middle line:90%
He's unique.

00:01:20.290 --> 00:01:22.700 align:middle line:90%
He attracts a lot of interest.

00:01:22.700 --> 00:01:25.024 align:middle line:84%
And he generates a
lot of storytelling.

00:01:25.024 --> 00:01:27.810 align:middle line:90%


00:01:27.810 --> 00:01:30.060 align:middle line:90%
>> It's an enigmatic shape.

00:01:30.060 --> 00:01:32.460 align:middle line:84%
No one knows when it
dates from or who made it.

00:01:32.460 --> 00:01:36.810 align:middle line:90%


00:01:36.810 --> 00:01:41.340 align:middle line:84%
>> We can't be sure why it
was made in the first place.

00:01:41.340 --> 00:01:44.100 align:middle line:84%
So these things are
mysterious fundamentally.

00:01:44.100 --> 00:01:48.020 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:01:48.020 --> 00:02:03.700 align:middle line:90%


00:02:03.700 --> 00:02:06.610 align:middle line:84%
>> We will go to England, where
many geoglyphs can be found.

00:02:06.610 --> 00:02:10.940 align:middle line:90%


00:02:10.940 --> 00:02:14.330 align:middle line:84%
We will also visit South
America, in the Atacama Desert,

00:02:14.330 --> 00:02:16.940 align:middle line:84%
where different peoples at
different moments in history

00:02:16.940 --> 00:02:19.090 align:middle line:84%
have left these mysterious
designs in the ground.

00:02:19.090 --> 00:02:22.260 align:middle line:90%


00:02:22.260 --> 00:02:26.410 align:middle line:84%
Let us begin with the most
enigmatic, the Nazca Lines.

00:02:26.410 --> 00:02:30.370 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:02:30.370 --> 00:02:39.290 align:middle line:90%


00:02:39.290 --> 00:02:41.360 align:middle line:84%
Every year,
thousands of tourists

00:02:41.360 --> 00:02:44.180 align:middle line:84%
cross the Atacama Desert
in Peru to come face

00:02:44.180 --> 00:02:46.940 align:middle line:84%
to face with one of the
greatest mysteries of humanity's

00:02:46.940 --> 00:02:48.610 align:middle line:90%
history.

00:02:48.610 --> 00:02:50.470 align:middle line:84%
Of all the geoglyphs
in the world,

00:02:50.470 --> 00:02:53.330 align:middle line:84%
the Nazca Lines are
certainly the most famous.

00:02:53.330 --> 00:02:55.960 align:middle line:84%
However, upon arrival,
there is just a desert

00:02:55.960 --> 00:02:59.050 align:middle line:84%
plain to be found, a
jumble of stones and dust

00:02:59.050 --> 00:03:01.360 align:middle line:84%
with nothing at all
growing and no sign

00:03:01.360 --> 00:03:03.670 align:middle line:90%
of any archaeological treasure.

00:03:03.670 --> 00:03:05.510 align:middle line:84%
Only by getting
up onto a platform

00:03:05.510 --> 00:03:07.690 align:middle line:84%
can a small part of the
puzzle here be seen.

00:03:07.690 --> 00:03:12.150 align:middle line:90%


00:03:12.150 --> 00:03:15.270 align:middle line:84%
Two figures are visible,
a tree and a hand.

00:03:15.270 --> 00:03:16.890 align:middle line:84%
As well, there are
long straight lines

00:03:16.890 --> 00:03:19.440 align:middle line:84%
stretching out
towards the horizon.

00:03:19.440 --> 00:03:21.060 align:middle line:84%
But to fully
comprehend the beauty

00:03:21.060 --> 00:03:23.930 align:middle line:84%
of the geoglyphs of Nazca,
they must be seen from above.

00:03:23.930 --> 00:03:31.890 align:middle line:90%


00:03:31.890 --> 00:03:35.250 align:middle line:84%
Since the only way to see the
lines properly is from a plane,

00:03:35.250 --> 00:03:36.900 align:middle line:90%
flights are in great demand.

00:03:36.900 --> 00:03:39.200 align:middle line:84%
Nazca Airport is the
second biggest in Peru.

00:03:39.200 --> 00:03:44.360 align:middle line:90%


00:03:44.360 --> 00:03:47.130 align:middle line:84%
>> The lines can be
seen from raised ground,

00:03:47.130 --> 00:03:49.860 align:middle line:84%
but in my opinion the clearest
view of the lines is surely

00:03:49.860 --> 00:03:51.630 align:middle line:90%
to see them from a plane.

00:03:51.630 --> 00:03:54.570 align:middle line:84%
From the sky, you can best see
the true shapes of the lines.

00:03:54.570 --> 00:03:57.990 align:middle line:90%


00:03:57.990 --> 00:03:59.490 align:middle line:90%
>> We came from Korea.

00:03:59.490 --> 00:04:01.710 align:middle line:84%
Now, after waiting
for 45 minutes,

00:04:01.710 --> 00:04:04.950 align:middle line:84%
we'll be able to see
the lines from a plane.

00:04:04.950 --> 00:04:07.560 align:middle line:84%
>> I've seen so many
reports on this and photos.

00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:09.060 align:middle line:84%
There's a lot of
mystery surrounding

00:04:09.060 --> 00:04:13.530 align:middle line:84%
this, where it came from, who
made it, how they made it.

00:04:13.530 --> 00:04:16.990 align:middle line:84%
>> Since no one can explain
scientifically what they are,

00:04:16.990 --> 00:04:20.040 align:middle line:84%
what they mean, or
why they were made,

00:04:20.040 --> 00:04:22.920 align:middle line:84%
we've come here ourselves to
get an idea of what these lines

00:04:22.920 --> 00:04:23.916 align:middle line:90%
represent.

00:04:23.916 --> 00:04:25.374 align:middle line:90%


00:04:25.374 --> 00:04:29.262 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:04:29.262 --> 00:04:34.140 align:middle line:90%


00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:36.890 align:middle line:84%
>> But a sandstorm
rises over the town.

00:04:36.890 --> 00:04:38.520 align:middle line:90%
All flights are canceled.

00:04:38.520 --> 00:04:40.760 align:middle line:84%
Our pilot, Eduardo
Herran, offers

00:04:40.760 --> 00:04:45.080 align:middle line:84%
to take us as close as
possible to the lines.

00:04:45.080 --> 00:04:46.730 align:middle line:90%
Eduardo isn't just a pilot.

00:04:46.730 --> 00:04:49.070 align:middle line:84%
He's fascinated by
the Nazca Lines.

00:04:49.070 --> 00:04:51.785 align:middle line:84%
Aboard his microlight plane,
he has discovered hundreds.

00:04:51.785 --> 00:04:54.780 align:middle line:90%


00:04:54.780 --> 00:04:56.860 align:middle line:90%
He takes us to the edge of town.

00:04:56.860 --> 00:05:00.420 align:middle line:84%
This is where El Tela, the
weaving loom, is to be found.

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:04.560 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the rare geoglyphs
that can be closely approached,

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:06.300 align:middle line:84%
and which allows
us to understand

00:05:06.300 --> 00:05:07.530 align:middle line:90%
how these lines were traced.

00:05:07.530 --> 00:05:14.890 align:middle line:90%


00:05:14.890 --> 00:05:18.070 align:middle line:90%
>> In reality, it's very simple.

00:05:18.070 --> 00:05:22.720 align:middle line:84%
The stones are pushed to the
sides and the center is swept.

00:05:22.720 --> 00:05:25.150 align:middle line:84%
This means that a layer which
has more white clay in it

00:05:25.150 --> 00:05:27.490 align:middle line:84%
stands out against
the dark surface.

00:05:27.490 --> 00:05:29.830 align:middle line:90%
This is how the lines were made.

00:05:29.830 --> 00:05:32.990 align:middle line:84%
It's really not
very complicated.

00:05:32.990 --> 00:05:36.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Most of the lines could have
been made with simple tools

00:05:36.070 --> 00:05:38.290 align:middle line:84%
such as stakes of
wood and ropes.

00:05:38.290 --> 00:05:41.320 align:middle line:84%
But their precision proves
that the Nazca civilization

00:05:41.320 --> 00:05:43.270 align:middle line:90%
understood mathematics.

00:05:43.270 --> 00:05:45.490 align:middle line:84%
Many people, like
Eduardo, are convinced

00:05:45.490 --> 00:05:48.130 align:middle line:84%
that the Nazcas had some way
of getting up high so they

00:05:48.130 --> 00:05:51.470 align:middle line:90%
could check their work.

00:05:51.470 --> 00:05:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>> From the ground, they're
not easy to make out.

00:05:55.130 --> 00:05:57.820 align:middle line:84%
And what we can see from
here is rather shapeless.

00:05:57.820 --> 00:06:00.360 align:middle line:90%


00:06:00.360 --> 00:06:02.990 align:middle line:84%
But the further up
in the sky you are,

00:06:02.990 --> 00:06:05.080 align:middle line:84%
the easier it is to see
what these people were

00:06:05.080 --> 00:06:08.065 align:middle line:90%
trying to say to us.

00:06:08.065 --> 00:06:11.500 align:middle line:84%
So if you ask me whether the
ancient people could fly,

00:06:11.500 --> 00:06:12.490 align:middle line:90%
I would say yes.

00:06:12.490 --> 00:06:15.470 align:middle line:90%


00:06:15.470 --> 00:06:18.420 align:middle line:84%
I think they used kites made
from canvas and feathers

00:06:18.420 --> 00:06:19.540 align:middle line:90%
to look at their work.

00:06:19.540 --> 00:06:22.930 align:middle line:90%


00:06:22.930 --> 00:06:25.450 align:middle line:84%
>> Another of the mysteries
of the Nazca Lines is

00:06:25.450 --> 00:06:27.520 align:middle line:90%
their incredible longevity.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:29.950 align:middle line:84%
They can still be
seen after 2,000 years

00:06:29.950 --> 00:06:32.890 align:middle line:84%
without anyone
looking after them.

00:06:32.890 --> 00:06:35.130 align:middle line:84%
The first reason for
that is geographic.

00:06:35.130 --> 00:06:37.660 align:middle line:84%
The lines are in the most
arid desert on the planet,

00:06:37.660 --> 00:06:40.720 align:middle line:84%
where it never rains and
where vegetation is rare.

00:06:40.720 --> 00:06:43.420 align:middle line:84%
The absence of humidity means
there is very little erosion.

00:06:43.420 --> 00:06:46.540 align:middle line:90%


00:06:46.540 --> 00:06:48.840 align:middle line:84%
But sandstorms can also
play a part in this.

00:06:48.840 --> 00:06:58.040 align:middle line:90%


00:06:58.040 --> 00:07:01.790 align:middle line:84%
>> All the surface dust is
pulled off as if the lines were

00:07:01.790 --> 00:07:04.725 align:middle line:90%
being swept.

00:07:04.725 --> 00:07:07.820 align:middle line:84%
So after one of
these storms, I like

00:07:07.820 --> 00:07:10.505 align:middle line:84%
to fly my microlight
because it's possible

00:07:10.505 --> 00:07:14.600 align:middle line:84%
that the winds have
made new marks visible.

00:07:14.600 --> 00:07:19.320 align:middle line:84%
I think the ancient people knew
about this effect of the wind

00:07:19.320 --> 00:07:22.745 align:middle line:84%
and used it as a maintenance
system to keep the lines clear.

00:07:22.745 --> 00:07:31.970 align:middle line:90%


00:07:31.970 --> 00:07:34.820 align:middle line:84%
>> Next morning, the
sandstorm has died down.

00:07:34.820 --> 00:07:38.972 align:middle line:84%
Flights progressively
start again at the airport.

00:07:38.972 --> 00:07:42.956 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:07:42.956 --> 00:08:02.420 align:middle line:90%


00:08:02.420 --> 00:08:05.320 align:middle line:84%
After a few minutes flying,
the great straight lines

00:08:05.320 --> 00:08:07.130 align:middle line:90%
are the first that we can see.

00:08:07.130 --> 00:08:09.770 align:middle line:84%
They seem to stretch
out for kilometers.

00:08:09.770 --> 00:08:12.380 align:middle line:84%
Smaller designs can also
be seen, some of which

00:08:12.380 --> 00:08:14.210 align:middle line:90%
represent animals.

00:08:14.210 --> 00:08:16.710 align:middle line:84%
The monkey, the spider,
and the hummingbird

00:08:16.710 --> 00:08:19.030 align:middle line:84%
are only some of the
hundreds of geoglyphs

00:08:19.030 --> 00:08:20.170 align:middle line:90%
to be found on the plain.

00:08:20.170 --> 00:08:22.930 align:middle line:90%


00:08:22.930 --> 00:08:26.540 align:middle line:84%
Anyone flying over these lines
is struck by these questions.

00:08:26.540 --> 00:08:27.440 align:middle line:90%
Who made this?

00:08:27.440 --> 00:08:28.390 align:middle line:90%
Why?

00:08:28.390 --> 00:08:31.460 align:middle line:84%
How can these marks be
so precise, so straight?

00:08:31.460 --> 00:08:33.209 align:middle line:84%
And what was the meaning
of these symbols?

00:08:33.209 --> 00:08:35.750 align:middle line:90%


00:08:35.750 --> 00:08:43.620 align:middle line:84%
Why did this tradition of line
tracing last over 1,000 years?

00:08:43.620 --> 00:08:46.290 align:middle line:84%
And everyone at Nazca
has their own explanation

00:08:46.290 --> 00:08:47.934 align:middle line:90%
of the lines' origin.

00:08:47.934 --> 00:08:49.350 align:middle line:84%
The straight lines
could have been

00:08:49.350 --> 00:08:53.437 align:middle line:84%
sacred ways where gatherings
or sacrifices took place.

00:08:53.437 --> 00:08:55.020 align:middle line:84%
Other people think
the lines were part

00:08:55.020 --> 00:08:57.290 align:middle line:90%
of a cult of mountain worship.

00:08:57.290 --> 00:09:00.240 align:middle line:84%
The zaniest explanation
comes from a writer coming up

00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:01.950 align:middle line:84%
with the idea that
the lines could

00:09:01.950 --> 00:09:05.580 align:middle line:84%
have been used as a landing
field by extraterrestrials.

00:09:05.580 --> 00:09:08.640 align:middle line:84%
This hypothesis is reinforced
by a mysterious design

00:09:08.640 --> 00:09:11.450 align:middle line:84%
on a mountainside which
could be an alien or a man

00:09:11.450 --> 00:09:12.450 align:middle line:90%
with the head of an owl.

00:09:12.450 --> 00:09:15.000 align:middle line:90%


00:09:15.000 --> 00:09:17.560 align:middle line:84%
>> What we can see here is
a model of the plane with

00:09:17.560 --> 00:09:19.660 align:middle line:90%
the lines.

00:09:19.660 --> 00:09:22.350 align:middle line:84%
This is only the commercialized
part of the area,

00:09:22.350 --> 00:09:26.550 align:middle line:84%
so to speak, where all
the flights are made.

00:09:26.550 --> 00:09:32.800 align:middle line:84%
Here you can find the monkey,
the dog, and the hummingbird.

00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:36.190 align:middle line:84%
But this just represents
10% of the lines.

00:09:36.190 --> 00:09:38.685 align:middle line:84%
We are confronted here
by a monumental document.

00:09:38.685 --> 00:09:43.100 align:middle line:90%


00:09:43.100 --> 00:09:45.230 align:middle line:84%
>> To better understand
the Nazca Lines,

00:09:45.230 --> 00:09:48.590 align:middle line:84%
we can try to tour around the
other geoglyphs on the planet.

00:09:48.590 --> 00:09:51.130 align:middle line:90%


00:09:51.130 --> 00:09:53.270 align:middle line:84%
While the Nazca Lines
are the most famous,

00:09:53.270 --> 00:09:55.300 align:middle line:90%
they're not the only geoglyphs.

00:09:55.300 --> 00:09:57.010 align:middle line:84%
Others are to be
found in England,

00:09:57.010 --> 00:10:01.962 align:middle line:84%
where dozens of what are called
Hill Figures can be found.

00:10:01.962 --> 00:10:06.444 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:10:06.444 --> 00:10:25.380 align:middle line:90%


00:10:25.380 --> 00:10:29.000 align:middle line:84%
The Wilmington Long Man
is at least 300 years old.

00:10:29.000 --> 00:10:31.730 align:middle line:84%
Neither its makers nor
the motives for its making

00:10:31.730 --> 00:10:32.660 align:middle line:90%
are known.

00:10:32.660 --> 00:10:35.690 align:middle line:84%
The figure was forgotten, then
rediscovered one fine day.

00:10:35.690 --> 00:10:39.080 align:middle line:84%
>> Up until the 19th century,
it had become grown over.

00:10:39.080 --> 00:10:41.180 align:middle line:84%
And there was a
woman living there

00:10:41.180 --> 00:10:44.040 align:middle line:84%
who noticed one day
when it had snowed

00:10:44.040 --> 00:10:48.020 align:middle line:84%
that the snow was melting to
reveal the image of a man,

00:10:48.020 --> 00:10:49.160 align:middle line:90%
of a figure.

00:10:49.160 --> 00:10:52.220 align:middle line:84%
Just because the snow was
melting slightly differently

00:10:52.220 --> 00:10:53.870 align:middle line:90%
in the channels.

00:10:53.870 --> 00:10:56.150 align:middle line:84%
And so this figure
came out of the snow,

00:10:56.150 --> 00:10:57.980 align:middle line:84%
and that's how it
was discovered.

00:10:57.980 --> 00:11:00.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Philip Carr-Gomm is a druid.

00:11:00.230 --> 00:11:03.290 align:middle line:84%
His relationship with the
giant began 20 years ago.

00:11:03.290 --> 00:11:06.740 align:middle line:84%
When one of his friends died, he
undertook a pilgrimage on foot

00:11:06.740 --> 00:11:09.960 align:middle line:84%
which ended at the
Wilmington Long Man.

00:11:09.960 --> 00:11:12.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The reason why you have these
figures in this particular part

00:11:12.990 --> 00:11:16.950 align:middle line:84%
of Britain is because the
topsoil is quite thin.

00:11:16.950 --> 00:11:18.930 align:middle line:84%
And so you have the
white chalk, and then you

00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:21.170 align:middle line:90%
have a thin layer of soil.

00:11:21.170 --> 00:11:25.500 align:middle line:84%
So it's very easy to cut down
with a spade and cut it out,

00:11:25.500 --> 00:11:29.500 align:middle line:84%
and then you can
see the white chalk.

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:32.380 align:middle line:84%
>> At one time, the chalk
could no longer be seen.

00:11:32.380 --> 00:11:33.880 align:middle line:84%
The marks were
therefore replaced

00:11:33.880 --> 00:11:35.710 align:middle line:90%
with cement painted white.

00:11:35.710 --> 00:11:37.930 align:middle line:84%
Despite these
restorations, the Long Man

00:11:37.930 --> 00:11:40.135 align:middle line:84%
remains a special place
for the region's druids.

00:11:40.135 --> 00:11:43.140 align:middle line:90%


00:11:43.140 --> 00:11:46.990 align:middle line:84%
>> In druidism, we treat
all of the Earth as sacred.

00:11:46.990 --> 00:11:49.320 align:middle line:84%
And there are also
special spots that

00:11:49.320 --> 00:11:52.750 align:middle line:84%
seem to be especially
sacred or very important.

00:11:52.750 --> 00:11:54.240 align:middle line:90%
And this is one such spot.

00:11:54.240 --> 00:11:57.420 align:middle line:84%
Eight times a year,
our local druid group

00:11:57.420 --> 00:11:58.886 align:middle line:90%
has a big festivity here.

00:11:58.886 --> 00:11:59.685 align:middle line:90%
Eight times a year.

00:11:59.685 --> 00:12:02.291 align:middle line:84%
The solstices, the
equinoxes, and so on.

00:12:02.291 --> 00:12:03.790 align:middle line:84%
If you were in
Wiltshire, if we were

00:12:03.790 --> 00:12:06.990 align:middle line:84%
in another part of England, we
would meet at a stone circle.

00:12:06.990 --> 00:12:08.920 align:middle line:84%
But here, we don't
have a stone circle.

00:12:08.920 --> 00:12:11.396 align:middle line:90%
Instead we meet here.

00:12:11.396 --> 00:12:15.520 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:12:15.520 --> 00:12:18.050 align:middle line:84%
>> Many legends
surround the giant.

00:12:18.050 --> 00:12:21.350 align:middle line:84%
Is it a lover sitting to
mourn the loss of his beloved?

00:12:21.350 --> 00:12:25.130 align:middle line:84%
A giant wounded by a stone
thrown by another giant?

00:12:25.130 --> 00:12:27.470 align:middle line:84%
Difficult to know
who made it and why.

00:12:27.470 --> 00:12:30.620 align:middle line:84%
But beyond the legends
that the design inspires,

00:12:30.620 --> 00:12:33.740 align:middle line:84%
Philip Carr-Gomm thinks that
the main thing is the effect

00:12:33.740 --> 00:12:37.750 align:middle line:90%
it has on people now.

00:12:37.750 --> 00:12:40.250 align:middle line:90%
>> And so it's a human figure.

00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:42.870 align:middle line:84%
And because it's
merely the outline,

00:12:42.870 --> 00:12:46.930 align:middle line:84%
it somehow symbolizes
every man, every woman.

00:12:46.930 --> 00:12:51.570 align:middle line:84%
And onto this very simple image,
we can project all our feelings

00:12:51.570 --> 00:12:55.900 align:middle line:84%
and our thoughts about humanity
and what it means to be human.

00:12:55.900 --> 00:12:58.980 align:middle line:84%
I think it's important
to find places for you

00:12:58.980 --> 00:13:01.620 align:middle line:84%
to go when either something
difficult has happened

00:13:01.620 --> 00:13:05.220 align:middle line:84%
in your life, or perhaps you
just need time on your own.

00:13:05.220 --> 00:13:08.631 align:middle line:84%
Life has become a little
stressful or difficult.

00:13:08.631 --> 00:13:12.110 align:middle line:90%
[DRUM MUSIC]

00:13:12.110 --> 00:13:17.090 align:middle line:90%


00:13:17.090 --> 00:13:21.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Geoglyphs can still play
a spiritual role for mankind.

00:13:21.110 --> 00:13:23.720 align:middle line:84%
And in Chile, people are
fighting to protect this

00:13:23.720 --> 00:13:28.900 align:middle line:84%
ancient cult. On the
Cerro Unitas Hill,

00:13:28.900 --> 00:13:31.930 align:middle line:84%
an 86 meter-long figure
has been contemplating

00:13:31.930 --> 00:13:34.390 align:middle line:90%
the plain for centuries.

00:13:34.390 --> 00:13:37.060 align:middle line:84%
The Atacama Giant was
made before the arrival

00:13:37.060 --> 00:13:41.650 align:middle line:84%
of the Spanish, between
the year 1,000 and 1,400.

00:13:41.650 --> 00:13:44.060 align:middle line:84%
The figure is the work
of the Aymara people,

00:13:44.060 --> 00:13:45.590 align:middle line:90%
and represents a Puma man.

00:13:45.590 --> 00:13:50.160 align:middle line:90%


00:13:50.160 --> 00:13:53.200 align:middle line:84%
>> The Atacama giant is
a very important place

00:13:53.200 --> 00:13:57.160 align:middle line:84%
for communication
with the cosmos.

00:13:57.160 --> 00:14:00.100 align:middle line:10%
It's a convergence point
for positive energy.

00:14:00.100 --> 00:14:03.320 align:middle line:90%


00:14:03.320 --> 00:14:06.610 align:middle line:84%
>> The Atacama Giant isn't the
only geoglyph on this hill.

00:14:06.610 --> 00:14:09.850 align:middle line:84%
There are also mysterious
circles, a feline design,

00:14:09.850 --> 00:14:10.820 align:middle line:90%
and human figures.

00:14:10.820 --> 00:14:13.680 align:middle line:90%


00:14:13.680 --> 00:14:16.630 align:middle line:84%
As at Nazca, the geoglyphs
have been drawn simply

00:14:16.630 --> 00:14:19.630 align:middle line:84%
by moving stones and have
lasted through time thanks

00:14:19.630 --> 00:14:23.730 align:middle line:84%
to the special
climate of the desert.

00:14:23.730 --> 00:14:25.970 align:middle line:84%
The Aymaran culture
behind these figures

00:14:25.970 --> 00:14:30.470 align:middle line:84%
is a people of 22 million spread
out over Chile, Peru, Bolivia,

00:14:30.470 --> 00:14:33.710 align:middle line:90%
and Argentina.

00:14:33.710 --> 00:14:36.410 align:middle line:84%
The Aymaran culture has a
deep respect for nature,

00:14:36.410 --> 00:14:38.220 align:middle line:84%
especially Mother
Earth, Pachamama.

00:14:38.220 --> 00:14:40.755 align:middle line:90%


00:14:40.755 --> 00:14:44.710 align:middle line:84%
Javier Vilca is fighting to
save and transmit this culture.

00:14:44.710 --> 00:14:48.200 align:middle line:90%


00:14:48.200 --> 00:14:52.340 align:middle line:84%
>> A long time ago, our
ancestors surely made offerings

00:14:52.340 --> 00:15:00.430 align:middle line:84%
to nature in this place to
bring rain, to demand plenty,

00:15:00.430 --> 00:15:05.960 align:middle line:84%
to calm the storms,
lessen the earthquakes,

00:15:05.960 --> 00:15:10.280 align:middle line:84%
surely because our
culture is integrated,

00:15:10.280 --> 00:15:17.510 align:middle line:84%
convivial and harmonious,
and respectful of nature.

00:15:17.510 --> 00:15:20.600 align:middle line:84%
>> For centuries there was
open access to the Giant,

00:15:20.600 --> 00:15:23.150 align:middle line:84%
and it was possible to
walk upon the lines.

00:15:23.150 --> 00:15:25.930 align:middle line:84%
But tourism and the
irresponsible behavior of some

00:15:25.930 --> 00:15:27.800 align:middle line:90%
menaced its protection.

00:15:27.800 --> 00:15:30.260 align:middle line:84%
For some years now, access
has been prohibited.

00:15:30.260 --> 00:15:35.060 align:middle line:90%


00:15:35.060 --> 00:15:37.970 align:middle line:90%
>> We can't go up on the hill.

00:15:37.970 --> 00:15:41.345 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to go up there
and see what's there.

00:15:41.345 --> 00:15:44.960 align:middle line:84%
At this distance, we can only
see that there's something.

00:15:44.960 --> 00:15:47.240 align:middle line:90%
But what is it?

00:15:47.240 --> 00:15:51.110 align:middle line:84%
I'd like to see to define
that more precisely.

00:15:51.110 --> 00:15:54.680 align:middle line:84%
It should be what we call a
sacred table, a place where you

00:15:54.680 --> 00:15:56.735 align:middle line:90%
can pray and give offerings.

00:15:56.735 --> 00:16:00.770 align:middle line:84%
But, well, the day will come
when we see these places return

00:16:00.770 --> 00:16:04.110 align:middle line:84%
to the indigenous people, the
true heirs of this culture.

00:16:04.110 --> 00:16:11.010 align:middle line:90%


00:16:11.010 --> 00:16:12.720 align:middle line:10%
>> After the arrival
of the Spanish,

00:16:12.720 --> 00:16:15.780 align:middle line:10%
different political regimes
tried to break up the Aymaran

00:16:15.780 --> 00:16:17.160 align:middle line:10%
culture.

00:16:17.160 --> 00:16:19.650 align:middle line:10%
Javier Vilca battles
daily to transmit

00:16:19.650 --> 00:16:23.070 align:middle line:10%
the knowledge of that
culture to new generations,

00:16:23.070 --> 00:16:25.440 align:middle line:10%
but it is difficult to
communicate and conserve

00:16:25.440 --> 00:16:26.610 align:middle line:10%
these traditions.

00:16:26.610 --> 00:16:28.080 align:middle line:84%
It's a different
view of the world

00:16:28.080 --> 00:16:29.913 align:middle line:84%
which has to be taught
anew to the youngest.

00:16:29.913 --> 00:16:33.160 align:middle line:90%


00:16:33.160 --> 00:16:36.775 align:middle line:84%
>> Our ancestors made their
offerings before going fishing

00:16:36.775 --> 00:16:40.220 align:middle line:90%
to the water god, [SPANISH].

00:16:40.220 --> 00:16:43.290 align:middle line:84%
They went to sea and
brought back their catch.

00:16:43.290 --> 00:16:45.967 align:middle line:84%
Why Because they had
implored their god

00:16:45.967 --> 00:16:47.175 align:middle line:90%
and the sea for its blessing.

00:16:47.175 --> 00:16:50.640 align:middle line:90%


00:16:50.640 --> 00:16:53.960 align:middle line:84%
The sea is an important
source of nutrition.

00:16:53.960 --> 00:16:55.970 align:middle line:90%
It feeds us.

00:16:55.970 --> 00:16:59.190 align:middle line:90%
It's something tremendous.

00:16:59.190 --> 00:17:01.760 align:middle line:84%
And because of that,
it must be loved.

00:17:01.760 --> 00:17:05.054 align:middle line:84%
It must be preserved, because
the sea brings benefits

00:17:05.054 --> 00:17:08.420 align:middle line:90%
to every one of us.

00:17:08.420 --> 00:17:12.340 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:17:12.340 --> 00:17:19.690 align:middle line:90%


00:17:19.690 --> 00:17:22.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Javier Vilca regrets that the
elements which would allow us

00:17:22.760 --> 00:17:25.970 align:middle line:84%
to decode the geoglyphs
have been lost over time.

00:17:25.970 --> 00:17:28.250 align:middle line:84%
He goes to the
Cerro Pintados site,

00:17:28.250 --> 00:17:31.010 align:middle line:84%
a few kilometers away
from the Atacama Giant.

00:17:31.010 --> 00:17:32.630 align:middle line:10%
Here, the whole
side of the mountain

00:17:32.630 --> 00:17:34.348 align:middle line:10%
is covered with geoglyphs.

00:17:34.348 --> 00:17:37.072 align:middle line:90%


00:17:37.072 --> 00:17:40.110 align:middle line:84%
>> There was an important
route which went from Altiplano

00:17:40.110 --> 00:17:43.170 align:middle line:90%
to the sea and passed by here.

00:17:43.170 --> 00:17:45.720 align:middle line:84%
We don't know since
when, but we do

00:17:45.720 --> 00:17:50.340 align:middle line:84%
know it has been here for
several thousand years.

00:17:50.340 --> 00:17:53.100 align:middle line:84%
We can't decode all
of this precisely

00:17:53.100 --> 00:17:55.362 align:middle line:84%
because our wise
men, the [SPANISH],,

00:17:55.362 --> 00:17:57.810 align:middle line:90%
are no longer with us.

00:17:57.810 --> 00:18:02.160 align:middle line:84%
They left when the
conquistadors arrived.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:05.400 align:middle line:84%
So amongst all the signs that
are here, there are only four

00:18:05.400 --> 00:18:10.280 align:middle line:84%
we can easily recognize and that
we still use in our weaving.

00:18:10.280 --> 00:18:15.240 align:middle line:84%
Like the water king, which
is represented by the toad.

00:18:15.240 --> 00:18:18.330 align:middle line:84%
We can also recognize the
marriage symbol, these two

00:18:18.330 --> 00:18:21.780 align:middle line:84%
little doves, which allow us
to see clearly which is the man

00:18:21.780 --> 00:18:24.810 align:middle line:90%
and which is the woman.

00:18:24.810 --> 00:18:27.930 align:middle line:84%
Then we have the llama, which
is a very important animal, part

00:18:27.930 --> 00:18:30.150 align:middle line:84%
of life for indigenous
Aymaran society.

00:18:30.150 --> 00:18:34.320 align:middle line:90%


00:18:34.320 --> 00:18:38.550 align:middle line:84%
There is also the sign
we call [SPANISH],, which

00:18:38.550 --> 00:18:41.730 align:middle line:84%
is a symbol we recognize and
preserve because it represents

00:18:41.730 --> 00:18:42.900 align:middle line:90%
the direction of life.

00:18:42.900 --> 00:18:48.590 align:middle line:90%


00:18:48.590 --> 00:18:51.510 align:middle line:84%
>> Geoglyphs still hold a
place in various beliefs.

00:18:51.510 --> 00:18:54.420 align:middle line:84%
Cults that are still dedicated
to them by some people

00:18:54.420 --> 00:18:55.980 align:middle line:84%
give us an idea
of the link there

00:18:55.980 --> 00:18:58.890 align:middle line:84%
could have been in the
past between the geoglyphs

00:18:58.890 --> 00:19:00.450 align:middle line:90%
and their makers.

00:19:00.450 --> 00:19:02.470 align:middle line:84%
The cults devoted
to the Nazca Lines

00:19:02.470 --> 00:19:04.470 align:middle line:84%
couldn't have been that
different to those still

00:19:04.470 --> 00:19:06.870 align:middle line:84%
existing today in
England and Chile,

00:19:06.870 --> 00:19:09.900 align:middle line:84%
but this knowledge has
been lost over time.

00:19:09.900 --> 00:19:13.320 align:middle line:84%
The Nazca Lines were only
rediscovered in 1924,

00:19:13.320 --> 00:19:16.700 align:middle line:84%
when planes began to
fly over South America.

00:19:16.700 --> 00:19:20.100 align:middle line:84%
But after 100 years of research,
their exact significance

00:19:20.100 --> 00:19:21.850 align:middle line:90%
remains an enigma.

00:19:21.850 --> 00:19:24.900 align:middle line:84%
The explanations given remain
for the moment just theories.

00:19:24.900 --> 00:19:26.925 align:middle line:84%
Like the lines, there
are a lot of theories.

00:19:26.925 --> 00:19:32.520 align:middle line:90%


00:19:32.520 --> 00:19:34.860 align:middle line:84%
It was a woman,
Maria Reiche, who

00:19:34.860 --> 00:19:36.780 align:middle line:84%
began to really
study the geoglyphs

00:19:36.780 --> 00:19:38.880 align:middle line:90%
in a scientific fashion.

00:19:38.880 --> 00:19:42.180 align:middle line:84%
In the 1940s, this
enthusiast devoted her life

00:19:42.180 --> 00:19:44.550 align:middle line:84%
to studying and
protecting the site.

00:19:44.550 --> 00:19:46.530 align:middle line:84%
Without her work
and obstination,

00:19:46.530 --> 00:19:49.050 align:middle line:84%
the lines would probably
have been destroyed.

00:19:49.050 --> 00:19:53.860 align:middle line:90%


00:19:53.860 --> 00:19:58.060 align:middle line:84%
After many years of study, Maria
Reiche ended up with a theory

00:19:58.060 --> 00:20:00.520 align:middle line:84%
that the lines are a
sort of star calendar,

00:20:00.520 --> 00:20:05.000 align:middle line:84%
and their orientation
is linked to the stars.

00:20:05.000 --> 00:20:07.510 align:middle line:84%
Maria Reiche discovered
that some of the lines

00:20:07.510 --> 00:20:10.090 align:middle line:84%
pointed to the solstice,
like those which crossed

00:20:10.090 --> 00:20:11.270 align:middle line:90%
the design of the spider.

00:20:11.270 --> 00:20:17.730 align:middle line:90%


00:20:17.730 --> 00:20:21.090 align:middle line:84%
So are the Nazca Lines
an immense calendar

00:20:21.090 --> 00:20:23.775 align:middle line:90%
drawn on the ground?

00:20:23.775 --> 00:20:27.735 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:20:27.735 --> 00:20:30.720 align:middle line:90%


00:20:30.720 --> 00:20:34.500 align:middle line:84%
Several hundred kilometers from
there on the Pacific coast,

00:20:34.500 --> 00:20:36.570 align:middle line:84%
another geoglyph
can perhaps help

00:20:36.570 --> 00:20:40.200 align:middle line:84%
us to understand the
mystery of the Nazca Lines.

00:20:40.200 --> 00:20:43.050 align:middle line:84%
The Candelabro de Paracas
is now in the heart

00:20:43.050 --> 00:20:44.680 align:middle line:90%
of a national park.

00:20:44.680 --> 00:20:46.650 align:middle line:84%
Land access is
impossible, and you

00:20:46.650 --> 00:20:49.380 align:middle line:84%
have to get there by boat
as thousands of tourists

00:20:49.380 --> 00:20:50.795 align:middle line:90%
do each year.

00:20:50.795 --> 00:20:54.190 align:middle line:90%
[BOAT ENGINE]

00:20:54.190 --> 00:20:57.870 align:middle line:90%


00:20:57.870 --> 00:21:00.580 align:middle line:84%
>> Juan Carlos Heaton, the
director of the reserve,

00:21:00.580 --> 00:21:02.650 align:middle line:84%
takes us to see the
famous Candelabra .

00:21:02.650 --> 00:21:06.690 align:middle line:90%


00:21:06.690 --> 00:21:08.760 align:middle line:84%
>> Many research
workers have come here.

00:21:08.760 --> 00:21:14.160 align:middle line:84%
One of them was Maria Reiche,
who was Peruvian and German.

00:21:14.160 --> 00:21:17.040 align:middle line:84%
She undertook astronomical
and mathematical research

00:21:17.040 --> 00:21:20.510 align:middle line:84%
on the lines and
shapes of Nazca.

00:21:20.510 --> 00:21:23.430 align:middle line:84%
She tried to make a
connection between the symbols

00:21:23.430 --> 00:21:25.940 align:middle line:84%
and an astronomical calendar
for the civilizations that

00:21:25.940 --> 00:21:26.740 align:middle line:90%
lived here.

00:21:26.740 --> 00:21:29.580 align:middle line:90%


00:21:29.580 --> 00:21:32.370 align:middle line:10%
In that context,
this figure is also

00:21:32.370 --> 00:21:35.940 align:middle line:10%
associated with
the Nazca culture.

00:21:35.940 --> 00:21:39.300 align:middle line:10%
The Candelabra has a lot to do
with astronomy and the Nazca

00:21:39.300 --> 00:21:43.115 align:middle line:10%
Lines, a theory which other
scientists have confirmed.

00:21:43.115 --> 00:21:46.710 align:middle line:90%


00:21:46.710 --> 00:21:49.290 align:middle line:84%
>> The Candelabra has all
the qualities of a compass.

00:21:49.290 --> 00:21:54.970 align:middle line:90%


00:21:54.970 --> 00:21:57.640 align:middle line:84%
>> This could be the
Southern Cross seen by day.

00:21:57.640 --> 00:21:59.440 align:middle line:84%
It has the same
direction with the top

00:21:59.440 --> 00:22:01.390 align:middle line:84%
of the Candelabra
showing the south,

00:22:01.390 --> 00:22:05.650 align:middle line:84%
and the base
signifying the north.

00:22:05.650 --> 00:22:07.870 align:middle line:84%
It resembles the
Southern Cross exactly,

00:22:07.870 --> 00:22:09.060 align:middle line:90%
according to Maria Reiche.

00:22:09.060 --> 00:22:12.250 align:middle line:90%


00:22:12.250 --> 00:22:14.680 align:middle line:84%
So this design could
serve as a reference

00:22:14.680 --> 00:22:18.790 align:middle line:90%
for daytime navigation.

00:22:18.790 --> 00:22:21.070 align:middle line:84%
We could also say that
this design functions

00:22:21.070 --> 00:22:22.535 align:middle line:90%
in the same way as a marker.

00:22:22.535 --> 00:22:26.734 align:middle line:90%


00:22:26.734 --> 00:22:29.810 align:middle line:84%
>> This simple trace in the
ground is actually visible out

00:22:29.810 --> 00:22:32.682 align:middle line:84%
at sea to a distance
of 20 kilometers,

00:22:32.682 --> 00:22:34.640 align:middle line:84%
but it's impossible to
know whether it was made

00:22:34.640 --> 00:22:37.865 align:middle line:84%
by navigators of antiquity
or by 17th century pirates.

00:22:37.865 --> 00:22:42.400 align:middle line:90%


00:22:42.400 --> 00:22:45.460 align:middle line:90%
>> We don't know its exact date.

00:22:45.460 --> 00:22:51.720 align:middle line:84%
Scientists can't tell if it
is 10,000 or 500 years old.

00:22:51.720 --> 00:22:54.700 align:middle line:84%
But we do know that
the pre-Incan ancestors

00:22:54.700 --> 00:22:57.790 align:middle line:84%
of Peruvians, as well
as the Incas themselves,

00:22:57.790 --> 00:23:01.480 align:middle line:90%
were very good navigators.

00:23:01.480 --> 00:23:03.820 align:middle line:84%
The whole coast of
Peru and South America

00:23:03.820 --> 00:23:06.130 align:middle line:84%
was known to the
Peruvians of antiquity.

00:23:06.130 --> 00:23:09.660 align:middle line:90%


00:23:09.660 --> 00:23:12.580 align:middle line:84%
>> The idea that Nazca is
an astronomical calendar is

00:23:12.580 --> 00:23:15.430 align:middle line:84%
attractive, but the great
majority of lines don't point

00:23:15.430 --> 00:23:17.530 align:middle line:90%
to any star or constellation.

00:23:17.530 --> 00:23:20.380 align:middle line:84%
Since the geoglyphs are
often visible from far off,

00:23:20.380 --> 00:23:22.780 align:middle line:84%
they've often been thought
of as a kind of sign post,

00:23:22.780 --> 00:23:25.406 align:middle line:90%
and not only in the desert.

00:23:25.406 --> 00:23:28.822 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:23:28.822 --> 00:23:38.610 align:middle line:90%


00:23:38.610 --> 00:23:41.580 align:middle line:84%
English geoglyphs are
mostly white horses.

00:23:41.580 --> 00:23:44.620 align:middle line:84%
There are nearly 20
across the country.

00:23:44.620 --> 00:23:47.380 align:middle line:84%
Amongst the oldest is the
Uffington White Horse.

00:23:47.380 --> 00:23:49.600 align:middle line:84%
It must be the first
in this long tradition,

00:23:49.600 --> 00:23:54.280 align:middle line:84%
as it dates from between 1,400
and 1,600 years before our era,

00:23:54.280 --> 00:23:57.460 align:middle line:84%
towards the end
