00:35:38.030 --> 00:35:40.850 align:middle line:90%
The Citadel of Cahuachi.

00:35:40.850 --> 00:35:45.190 align:middle line:84%
What can be seen today is just
a tiny part of a vast complex.

00:35:45.190 --> 00:35:48.370 align:middle line:84%
Soledad from the Archaeological
Service takes us there.

00:35:48.370 --> 00:35:54.370 align:middle line:90%


00:35:54.370 --> 00:35:58.430 align:middle line:10%
>> Excavations at
Cahuachi began in 1982.

00:35:58.430 --> 00:36:02.020 align:middle line:84%
But the entire
surface was buried.

00:36:02.020 --> 00:36:05.740 align:middle line:84%
Now we presume that just 5%
of the total archaeological

00:36:05.740 --> 00:36:08.770 align:middle line:84%
complex has been
brought to light.

00:36:08.770 --> 00:36:13.870 align:middle line:84%
So of course, there's a lot
more to dig up and discover.

00:36:13.870 --> 00:36:16.750 align:middle line:84%
>> Since they lack the means,
archaeologists are advancing

00:36:16.750 --> 00:36:18.670 align:middle line:90%
very slowly at the site.

00:36:18.670 --> 00:36:22.890 align:middle line:84%
But its purpose can
already be determined.

00:36:22.890 --> 00:36:27.160 align:middle line:84%
Cahuachi isn't a citadel as was
thought when it was discovered.

00:36:27.160 --> 00:36:30.280 align:middle line:84%
It was a religious center
which had incredible importance

00:36:30.280 --> 00:36:31.520 align:middle line:90%
in its time.

00:36:31.520 --> 00:36:34.420 align:middle line:84%
It stretched over
24 square kilometers

00:36:34.420 --> 00:36:37.174 align:middle line:84%
and welcomed thousands
of pilgrims each year.

00:36:37.174 --> 00:36:38.590 align:middle line:84%
At the time, it
was the equivalent

00:36:38.590 --> 00:36:41.820 align:middle line:90%
of Mecca or the Vatican.

00:36:41.820 --> 00:36:43.840 align:middle line:84%
>> There's a relationship
between the lines

00:36:43.840 --> 00:36:46.588 align:middle line:90%
and the citadel.

00:36:46.588 --> 00:36:49.480 align:middle line:84%
The geoglyphs are found in
front of the most important

00:36:49.480 --> 00:36:53.880 align:middle line:90%
ceremonial centers on the plain.

00:36:53.880 --> 00:36:55.510 align:middle line:84%
But at the back
part of the citadel,

00:36:55.510 --> 00:37:00.010 align:middle line:84%
we've also found a variety of
lines and trapezoids, geoglyphs

00:37:00.010 --> 00:37:04.420 align:middle line:84%
which have an important
link with Cahuachi.

00:37:04.420 --> 00:37:06.880 align:middle line:84%
The same civilization
which build the citadel

00:37:06.880 --> 00:37:07.860 align:middle line:90%
made the geoglyphs.

00:37:07.860 --> 00:37:12.400 align:middle line:90%


00:37:12.400 --> 00:37:14.620 align:middle line:84%
As for their impressive
size, the people

00:37:14.620 --> 00:37:17.080 align:middle line:84%
here must have considered
that their gods could

00:37:17.080 --> 00:37:18.750 align:middle line:90%
contemplate the geoglyphs.

00:37:18.750 --> 00:37:21.910 align:middle line:90%


00:37:21.910 --> 00:37:25.360 align:middle line:84%
They were offerings to the gods,
made so they could see them.

00:37:25.360 --> 00:37:29.050 align:middle line:90%


00:37:29.050 --> 00:37:31.660 align:middle line:84%
>> People came from very
far away on pilgrimage,

00:37:31.660 --> 00:37:34.950 align:middle line:84%
and thousands of people lived
here to welcome the visitors.

00:37:34.950 --> 00:37:36.810 align:middle line:84%
The key to better
understanding of the lines

00:37:36.810 --> 00:37:40.380 align:middle line:84%
seems to be to better understand
the whole of this civilization,

00:37:40.380 --> 00:37:43.940 align:middle line:84%
but the Nazca did not only
leave behind their geoglyphs.

00:37:43.940 --> 00:37:46.440 align:middle line:84%
The lines are just one of
the many means of expression

00:37:46.440 --> 00:37:48.902 align:middle line:90%
used by this civilization.

00:37:48.902 --> 00:37:51.060 align:middle line:84%
Giuseppe Orefici is
one of the region's

00:37:51.060 --> 00:37:52.980 align:middle line:90%
principal archaeologists.

00:37:52.980 --> 00:37:55.560 align:middle line:90%


00:37:55.560 --> 00:37:58.890 align:middle line:84%
>> As we've seen, the Nazca
civilization was impressive

00:37:58.890 --> 00:38:02.130 align:middle line:84%
because it had many forms
of expression ranging from

00:38:02.130 --> 00:38:07.170 align:middle line:84%
ceramics to geoglyphs, as
well as all the other systems

00:38:07.170 --> 00:38:08.215 align:middle line:90%
of expression.

00:38:08.215 --> 00:38:11.690 align:middle line:90%


00:38:11.690 --> 00:38:15.240 align:middle line:84%
This shows us the grandeur
of this civilization which,

00:38:15.240 --> 00:38:18.330 align:middle line:84%
based on a theocracy, dominated
a very large territory

00:38:18.330 --> 00:38:22.710 align:middle line:90%
for over 1,000 years.

00:38:22.710 --> 00:38:25.320 align:middle line:84%
>> The Nazca civilization
was very advanced from

00:38:25.320 --> 00:38:29.160 align:middle line:84%
a technological point of view,
not just in irrigation but also

00:38:29.160 --> 00:38:32.230 align:middle line:84%
in construction, mathematics,
music, agriculture,

00:38:32.230 --> 00:38:33.030 align:middle line:90%
and pottery.

00:38:33.030 --> 00:38:36.330 align:middle line:90%


00:38:36.330 --> 00:38:39.990 align:middle line:84%
>> The iconographic themes which
are found in the Nazca Lines

00:38:39.990 --> 00:38:42.535 align:middle line:84%
show us that they had a great
ability to reproduce scale

00:38:42.535 --> 00:38:43.335 align:middle line:90%
drawings.

00:38:43.335 --> 00:38:46.110 align:middle line:90%


00:38:46.110 --> 00:38:48.360 align:middle line:84%
This was because they
managed to succeed

00:38:48.360 --> 00:38:52.410 align:middle line:84%
in reproducing using gigantic
lines the iconography found

00:38:52.410 --> 00:38:53.867 align:middle line:90%
on ceramics.

00:38:53.867 --> 00:38:57.346 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:38:57.346 --> 00:39:05.800 align:middle line:90%


00:39:05.800 --> 00:39:08.230 align:middle line:84%
>> With such a rich
and varied culture,

00:39:08.230 --> 00:39:11.590 align:middle line:84%
the diversity and precision of
the Nazca design seems a little

00:39:11.590 --> 00:39:13.520 align:middle line:90%
less astonishing.

00:39:13.520 --> 00:39:15.690 align:middle line:84%
But despite all
these discoveries,

00:39:15.690 --> 00:39:18.270 align:middle line:84%
the Nazca Lines keep
most of their secrets,

00:39:18.270 --> 00:39:20.340 align:middle line:84%
and it has to be accepted
that some of them

00:39:20.340 --> 00:39:23.490 align:middle line:90%
will always remain a mystery.

00:39:23.490 --> 00:39:26.280 align:middle line:84%
Doubtless in the years to
come, sleeping geoglyphs

00:39:26.280 --> 00:39:28.920 align:middle line:84%
will be discovered, especially
thanks to the growing

00:39:28.920 --> 00:39:31.590 align:middle line:90%
precision of satellite imagery.

00:39:31.590 --> 00:39:34.380 align:middle line:84%
So they will continue to
feed legend and generate

00:39:34.380 --> 00:39:36.890 align:middle line:90%
stories of the supernatural.

00:39:36.890 --> 00:39:39.300 align:middle line:84%
But the geoglyphs offer
us one last enigma.

00:39:39.300 --> 00:39:40.680 align:middle line:90%
What do we do with them now?

00:39:40.680 --> 00:39:46.540 align:middle line:90%


00:39:46.540 --> 00:39:49.110 align:middle line:84%
At Nazca, some
sites are protected,

00:39:49.110 --> 00:39:51.330 align:middle line:84%
but there are so many
designs spread out

00:39:51.330 --> 00:39:54.810 align:middle line:84%
over such a vast surface that
some have not even been listed.

00:39:54.810 --> 00:39:57.680 align:middle line:90%


00:39:57.680 --> 00:40:00.870 align:middle line:84%
And in Chile, on the
flanks of Cerros Pintados,

00:40:00.870 --> 00:40:05.010 align:middle line:84%
the great vulnerability
of the geoglyphs is clear.

00:40:05.010 --> 00:40:07.430 align:middle line:84%
The enormous fresco is
pierced with holes that

00:40:07.430 --> 00:40:09.780 align:middle line:90%
have degraded the geoglyphs.

00:40:09.780 --> 00:40:11.700 align:middle line:84%
This is because of
mining prospecting,

00:40:11.700 --> 00:40:14.700 align:middle line:84%
looking for saltpeter deposits
at the end of the 19th century.

00:40:14.700 --> 00:40:19.810 align:middle line:90%


00:40:19.810 --> 00:40:22.720 align:middle line:84%
>> Here we can see the traces
of those which were degraded

00:40:22.720 --> 00:40:28.030 align:middle line:84%
and destroyed because people
at the time of saltpeter mining

00:40:28.030 --> 00:40:30.635 align:middle line:84%
didn't have the slightest idea
of the value of this giant

00:40:30.635 --> 00:40:31.435 align:middle line:90%
message.

00:40:31.435 --> 00:40:34.170 align:middle line:90%


00:40:34.170 --> 00:40:37.450 align:middle line:84%
They called these places
the Painted Mountains,

00:40:37.450 --> 00:40:39.740 align:middle line:84%
but in reality
they're not paintings

00:40:39.740 --> 00:40:41.900 align:middle line:84%
and this has nothing to
do with the original name

00:40:41.900 --> 00:40:42.700 align:middle line:90%
of the mountains.

00:40:42.700 --> 00:40:45.465 align:middle line:90%


00:40:45.465 --> 00:40:48.910 align:middle line:84%
This shows their ignorance of
the value of the geoglyphs,

00:40:48.910 --> 00:40:50.110 align:middle line:90%
which are so important.

00:40:50.110 --> 00:40:53.050 align:middle line:90%


00:40:53.050 --> 00:40:56.320 align:middle line:84%
Today, at least the intention
is to protect these.

00:40:56.320 --> 00:41:00.070 align:middle line:90%


00:41:00.070 --> 00:41:03.100 align:middle line:84%
Because these ceremonial
sites were sacred,

00:41:03.100 --> 00:41:06.340 align:middle line:84%
they need to be given
back that value.

00:41:06.340 --> 00:41:08.600 align:middle line:84%
As these sites are
returned to us,

00:41:08.600 --> 00:41:10.630 align:middle line:84%
we'll re-establish
the great harmony

00:41:10.630 --> 00:41:12.130 align:middle line:90%
with nature that once existed.

00:41:12.130 --> 00:41:21.560 align:middle line:90%


00:41:21.560 --> 00:41:24.080 align:middle line:84%
>> But protecting
them isn't enough.

00:41:24.080 --> 00:41:28.837 align:middle line:84%
Most geoglyphs risk disappearing
if they are not maintained.

00:41:28.837 --> 00:41:32.749 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:41:32.749 --> 00:41:40.580 align:middle line:90%


00:41:40.580 --> 00:41:43.670 align:middle line:84%
On the same site as the
Nazcas, an even more

00:41:43.670 --> 00:41:45.980 align:middle line:84%
ancient civilization
had begun to create

00:41:45.980 --> 00:41:49.550 align:middle line:90%
geoglyphs, the Paracas.

00:41:49.550 --> 00:41:51.410 align:middle line:84%
These designs had
almost disappeared

00:41:51.410 --> 00:41:54.800 align:middle line:84%
and were very difficult to
see, so a restoration campaign

00:41:54.800 --> 00:41:56.510 align:middle line:90%
was begun.

00:41:56.510 --> 00:41:59.510 align:middle line:84%
Johny Isla, Director of
the Archaeological Service,

00:41:59.510 --> 00:42:03.890 align:middle line:84%
comes with his team to
restore the precious designs.

00:42:03.890 --> 00:42:06.380 align:middle line:84%
>> What we're going to do is
take some photographs so that

00:42:06.380 --> 00:42:08.000 align:middle line:90%
we can get a scale.

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:11.170 align:middle line:84%
After that, the piles of stones
weren't there originally,

00:42:11.170 --> 00:42:12.539 align:middle line:90%
so we'll take them away.

00:42:12.539 --> 00:42:14.330 align:middle line:84%
Practically, that's
what we're going to do.

00:42:14.330 --> 00:42:20.200 align:middle line:90%


00:42:20.200 --> 00:42:23.690 align:middle line:84%
At the Palpa site, we've
identified nearly 80 groups

00:42:23.690 --> 00:42:26.350 align:middle line:90%
of figures of this type.

00:42:26.350 --> 00:42:29.220 align:middle line:84%
They were all
disappearing because they

00:42:29.220 --> 00:42:31.550 align:middle line:84%
had been made on
the mountain slopes

00:42:31.550 --> 00:42:35.210 align:middle line:84%
where there's a lot of erosion,
sometimes rain, people passing

00:42:35.210 --> 00:42:38.130 align:middle line:84%
by, earth movements, and
also dust and wind which

00:42:38.130 --> 00:42:38.930 align:middle line:90%
caused erosion.

00:42:38.930 --> 00:42:42.530 align:middle line:90%


00:42:42.530 --> 00:42:47.280 align:middle line:84%
We identified several different
groups, such as this one here,

00:42:47.280 --> 00:42:49.550 align:middle line:84%
which has been restored
by putting the stones back

00:42:49.550 --> 00:42:52.280 align:middle line:84%
in place, which makes
the figure more visible.

00:42:52.280 --> 00:42:54.870 align:middle line:90%


00:42:54.870 --> 00:42:57.440 align:middle line:84%
Basically what we're doing
is lifting the stones which

00:42:57.440 --> 00:43:00.230 align:middle line:84%
have fallen inside the
figures and putting them back

00:43:00.230 --> 00:43:04.100 align:middle line:84%
on the sides so that the figure
keeps its original contours,

00:43:04.100 --> 00:43:06.350 align:middle line:84%
and in that way it can
be seen from far off.

00:43:06.350 --> 00:43:09.700 align:middle line:90%


00:43:09.700 --> 00:43:12.040 align:middle line:84%
It's a technique which
we use for buildings,

00:43:12.040 --> 00:43:14.390 align:middle line:84%
but with geoglyphs
it's the first time

00:43:14.390 --> 00:43:17.090 align:middle line:84%
that we've used it to bring them
back to their original state.

00:43:17.090 --> 00:43:21.170 align:middle line:90%


00:43:21.170 --> 00:43:23.720 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we have to clear
away the earth that builds up

00:43:23.720 --> 00:43:27.830 align:middle line:84%
on the stone with
brushes and nothing else,

00:43:27.830 --> 00:43:30.320 align:middle line:84%
and in some cases when
we're restoring them

00:43:30.320 --> 00:43:33.200 align:middle line:84%
we use a little water to
clean the stones so as

00:43:33.200 --> 00:43:36.540 align:middle line:90%
to make them more visible.

00:43:36.540 --> 00:43:38.170 align:middle line:90%
Nothing more.

00:43:38.170 --> 00:43:41.730 align:middle line:84%
It's a very simple technique,
but it takes a lot of time.

00:43:41.730 --> 00:43:50.055 align:middle line:90%


00:43:50.055 --> 00:43:54.110 align:middle line:10%
>> We clean them carefully, just
enough to be able to visualize

00:43:54.110 --> 00:43:58.045 align:middle line:10%
them without altering them.

00:43:58.045 --> 00:44:01.496 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:44:01.496 --> 00:44:22.730 align:middle line:90%


00:44:22.730 --> 00:44:26.000 align:middle line:84%
>> Maintenance and restoration
are also part of daily life

00:44:26.000 --> 00:44:28.760 align:middle line:84%
around the Uffington
White Horse.

00:44:28.760 --> 00:44:33.110 align:middle line:84%
More than 250,000 people come
each year to visit the site

00:44:33.110 --> 00:44:38.234 align:middle line:84%
and to do all sorts of strange
things inspired by the legends.

00:44:38.234 --> 00:44:40.230 align:middle line:90%
>> Nice.

00:44:40.230 --> 00:44:44.120 align:middle line:84%
One is that if you stand in the
eye of the horse and you spin

00:44:44.120 --> 00:44:47.660 align:middle line:84%
round three times, it
will bring you luck.

00:44:47.660 --> 00:44:51.380 align:middle line:84%
But if I see you, I
will tell you off.

00:44:51.380 --> 00:44:52.430 align:middle line:90%
It's not good.

00:44:52.430 --> 00:44:54.430 align:middle line:84%
Erosion is one of
our biggest problems.

00:44:54.430 --> 00:44:59.465 align:middle line:84%
I mean, all this, this is
because of people stepping.

00:44:59.465 --> 00:45:02.480 align:middle line:84%
We ask don't step on the
horse, so they step here.

00:45:02.480 --> 00:45:06.530 align:middle line:84%
And then you multiply
this by thousands.

00:45:06.530 --> 00:45:09.110 align:middle line:84%
This is why you get marks
like this and like that.

00:45:09.110 --> 00:45:12.240 align:middle line:90%
It's where people step.

00:45:12.240 --> 00:45:13.040 align:middle line:90%
Every time.

00:45:13.040 --> 00:45:15.440 align:middle line:90%
That's a step, you see?

00:45:15.440 --> 00:45:18.560 align:middle line:90%
And that's the problem.

00:45:18.560 --> 00:45:20.670 align:middle line:90%
But it keeps me busy.

00:45:20.670 --> 00:45:24.080 align:middle line:84%
There is always
work to do here, OK?

00:45:24.080 --> 00:45:26.600 align:middle line:84%
>> But there's no question
of closing the site.

00:45:26.600 --> 00:45:29.870 align:middle line:84%
The powers that be want people
to have access to the horse

00:45:29.870 --> 00:45:31.170 align:middle line:90%
and to know its history.

00:45:31.170 --> 00:45:34.770 align:middle line:90%


00:45:34.770 --> 00:45:38.030 align:middle line:84%
So the geoglyph has to
be maintained every year.

00:45:38.030 --> 00:45:40.640 align:middle line:84%
400 people work in
relay over two days

00:45:40.640 --> 00:45:43.720 align:middle line:84%
to renew the surface
level of chalk.

00:45:43.720 --> 00:45:46.390 align:middle line:84%
>> This is how we
chalk the horse.

00:45:46.390 --> 00:45:49.610 align:middle line:84%
The method hasn't changed
in thousands of years.

00:45:49.610 --> 00:45:51.020 align:middle line:90%
It's exactly the same.

00:45:51.020 --> 00:45:52.270 align:middle line:90%
This is our technology.

00:45:52.270 --> 00:45:55.520 align:middle line:90%


00:45:55.520 --> 00:46:00.350 align:middle line:84%
We could, if we want, today
the men who make the roads,

00:46:00.350 --> 00:46:03.600 align:middle line:90%
they have the pneumatic--

00:46:03.600 --> 00:46:04.670 align:middle line:90%
you know?

00:46:04.670 --> 00:46:08.540 align:middle line:84%
Yes, you could do that here,
but it's not the same, is it?

00:46:08.540 --> 00:46:09.920 align:middle line:90%
It's not the story.

00:46:09.920 --> 00:46:11.120 align:middle line:90%
We want to do it.

00:46:11.120 --> 00:46:13.130 align:middle line:90%
We want to keep tradition alive.

00:46:13.130 --> 00:46:14.550 align:middle line:90%
That's what it's all about.

00:46:14.550 --> 00:46:17.450 align:middle line:84%
This is our heritage,
the heritage of England.

00:46:17.450 --> 00:46:19.020 align:middle line:90%
So we want to keep it.

00:46:19.020 --> 00:46:20.990 align:middle line:84%
We want to use
people, not machines.

00:46:20.990 --> 00:46:23.660 align:middle line:90%


00:46:23.660 --> 00:46:26.630 align:middle line:84%
>> The Uffington White Horse
has thus been looked after from

00:46:26.630 --> 00:46:30.410 align:middle line:84%
generation to generation
for over 3,000 years.

00:46:30.410 --> 00:46:32.570 align:middle line:84%
Elsewhere in the
country, other geoglyphs

00:46:32.570 --> 00:46:34.790 align:middle line:84%
have been lost for
lack of maintenance,

00:46:34.790 --> 00:46:38.420 align:middle line:84%
and covered back
over by vegetation.

00:46:38.420 --> 00:46:40.520 align:middle line:84%
Today, English Hill
Figures are mainly

00:46:40.520 --> 00:46:46.040 align:middle line:84%
looked after by institutions
or groups of local inhabitants.

00:46:46.040 --> 00:46:48.610 align:middle line:84%
Some are still made,
keeping the tradition alive.

00:46:48.610 --> 00:46:52.330 align:middle line:90%


00:46:52.330 --> 00:46:54.730 align:middle line:84%
The latest was
made in 2006, near

00:46:54.730 --> 00:46:56.620 align:middle line:90%
to the Channel Tunnel entrance.

00:46:56.620 --> 00:47:00.540 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:47:00.540 --> 00:47:10.840 align:middle line:90%


00:47:10.840 --> 00:47:14.310 align:middle line:84%
In 1990, Katherine launched
a project with her students.

00:47:14.310 --> 00:47:24.050 align:middle line:90%


00:47:24.050 --> 00:47:25.890 align:middle line:10%
>> In the months
following the trial,

00:47:25.890 --> 00:47:29.010 align:middle line:10%
I thought it would be an
interesting thing to do

00:47:29.010 --> 00:47:33.030 align:middle line:10%
to conduct some exercise
in experimental archeology,

00:47:33.030 --> 00:47:37.340 align:middle line:10%
and to tape out a
giantess, a Hill Figure.

00:47:37.340 --> 00:47:41.010 align:middle line:90%


